  "title": "Plating Maintenance Engineer",
  "description": "<p>1.     Organise long term planning for plating facilities, equipment and installation inclusive of<br />-       \nrepair and breakdown support</p><p>-       preventive maintenance program</p><p>2.     Design and execute engineering project (related to equipment etc) in accordance with specification and safe practice.</p><p>3.     Lead maintenance team to perform new plating equipment training.</p><p>4.     To fully understanding management requirement and fulfill the commitment.</p><p>5.     Follow schedule to complete equipment maintenance & calibration.</p><p>6.     Evaluate new equipment applied to plating improvement and training production technician to fully handle new equipments.</p><p>7.     Assist in the development and maintain of methods/procedure and/or systems which comply with ISO or other applicable requirements</p><p>8.     Carry out all general maintenance work on plating line equipment, ie motor, pump rectifier etc.</p><p>9.     Carry out installation and modification of machines and equipment </p><p>10.  Carry out general electrical works, repairs, troubleshooting and maintenance of machines and equipment in plating department.</p><p>11.  Support DI/waste treatment operation </p><p>12.  Liaise with vendor to do repair on equipment or process.</p><p>13.  Purchase component and spare part related to electrical and control item to minimize the cost.</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>·      Above 10 years experiences with NTC grade 3 in Electrical or Mechanical Or Diploma / Degree in Engineering (Mechanical or Electrical Engineering)</p><p>·       More than 3 years of working experience in reel-to-reel plating maintenance environment</p><p>·       Able to read electrical drawing and Autocad experience</p><p>·       Able to work independently with minimum guidance.</p>",
